# Photo Fun Project Rules

## Project Overview
This is a React + Vite web application for AI-powered photo editing using Google's Gemini API.

## Tech Stack
- React 19
- TypeScript
- Vite
- Tailwind CSS (via CDN)
- Google Gemini API (@google/genai)

## Code Style
- Use TypeScript for all new files
- Use functional components with hooks
- Follow existing component structure
- Use Tailwind CSS classes for styling

## Environment Variables
- API keys should be stored in `.env.local` (gitignored)
- Use `GEMINI_API_KEY` for the Gemini API key
- Never commit `.env.local` or actual API keys

## File Organization
- Components in `components/` directory
- Services in `services/` directory
- Types in `types.ts`
- Constants in `constants.ts`

## Important Notes
- The app uses `import.meta.env.VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY` or `process.env.GEMINI_API_KEY` for API key access
- Vite config handles environment variable exposure via `define`
- The app is designed to work without AI Studio dependencies
